observations.recommendation:
We recommended the following:

The Local Chief Executive (LCE), thru the City Administrator (CA) –

Require the CGSO and CAO, to ensure compliance with the activities outlined in the PIP, to come up with the initial reconciled balances of PPE accounts, prior to the conduct of physical count of the Composite Inventory Team; 

Require the Composite Inventory Team on PPE accounts to undertake and complete the physical Inventory of Property, and conduct the final reconciliation with the property and accounting records. The Inventory Team shall be required to render a report on completion and reconciliation of the PPE accounts within the prescribed timetable outlined in the PIP;

The Property Custodian/Officer, CGSO, Procurement Office and 
CAO –

Ensure compliance with the activities outlined in the approved PIP;

Set-up an effective system to keep track and capture the related transactions on PPE and PARs; implement the use of inventory tag; reconcile PPE records regularly and adjust accordingly; and to promptly reconcile the results of the physical count with the accountabilities recorded in the books of accounts and the property cards during the preliminary activities and upon completion of inventory count, as defined in the approved PIP; and

Submit the completed and reconciled RPCPPE to the Auditor within the prescribed period in accordance with Section 124 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I.

We further recommended to assign employees with full dedication and integrity to work at the Property Division of CGSO for the tasks involving the custodial, inventory and coordination with concerned Offices regarding the City’s properties.

We recommended to comply with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2002-003 dated June 20, 2002 or the MNGAS, Volume I, on the manner of recording the inventory accounts and recognition of corresponding expense accounts, as follows:

The Procurement Office to provide CGSO, copy of POs or contracts for the procured supplies, materials and goods immediately after perfection of the contract.  The POs shall serve as reference of the CGSO on the delivery terms and for the subsequent preparations of AIRs and recording of eventual inventories/equipment in their records;

The CGSO to –

To coordinate with the designated Procurement Office and the City Accountant’s Office, on a periodic basis, on the status of POs or contracts’ issuance for the procured supplies, materials and goods;

Based on the POs provided by the designated Procurement Office, document the acceptance, inspection and recording of inventories/equipment thru the use of the AIR completely filled up with the necessary information and complete documentation

To require from end users and property officer/warehouse keeper the submission of Utilization Report for the procurement made and to document the SSMI and RIS; 

To submit to CAO, after the acceptance on the deliveries of the procured supplies, materials and goods, copies of POs, AIRs and supporting documents for the recognition of Inventory accounts in the books; and the monthly Report of SSMI supported with RIS and documentation, for the recording of inventory utilization;

The CAO to –

To coordinate with CGSO, on a periodic basis, on the status of AIRs completion supported with POs and other documents; and

To see to it that the recorded inventory accounts shall be supported with AIR, sales invoices with delivery receipts and PO reference; and support the recorded utilization or issuance of supplies with SSMI and RIS with complete documentation.

We recommended that the Management, thru the Local Finance Committee:

Consider a systematic and realistic forecasting of revenue taking into account the prior years’ experience and statistics as aids in setting targets; 

Involve the CTO and other Departments in generating revenues to meet the targets;

Require the CTO to accomplish the Quarterly Report of Income to keep track of the status of revenue generation; and 

Require the concerned officials to conduct periodic review of the Quarterly Report of Income to ascertain whether collection targets are attained, to provide assurance of improved finances for the operations of the City.

We recommended that:
The CTO to –
Closely coordinate with the bank officials on the status of the requested copies of the bank’s credit and debit memos and other reconciling items for submission to the CAO to support the adjustments to the related assets and government equity accounts;
Regularly monitor checks issued to avoid stale checks and coordinate with CAO for any checks that were returned for replacement;
Notify the concerned payees of the issued staled checks, as to the status of their claim, to serve as reference in the possible cancellation and replacement of checks and/or reversion to Cash in Bank - LCCA, for those payees who are no longer interested to claim payments;
The CAO to –
Upon receipt of the documents from the CTO, prepare immediately the necessary entries for the reconciling items; and
Coordinate with the CTO for the immediate clearing of reconciling items pertaining to the difference of P6,408,293.60 between the bank and book beginning balance.

