Ensure full participation and involvement in all of the  inventory undertaking; and

Submit the completed and reconciled RPCPPE to the Auditor within the prescribed period in accordance with Section 124 of the Manual on the New Government Accounting System (MNGAS) for Local Government Units (LGUs), Volume I.

Formulate and set up policies or updating of service standards for the processing of payment of claims;

Require the head of the department concerned, to adhere to the requirement of COA Circular No. 2002-003 dated June 20, 2002, or MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I;

Consider the involvement of the City Accountant as member of Bids and Awards Committee (BAC) Secretariat or in the Technical Working Group in order to address the prolonged time in complying with the documentary requirements, initially at the procurement level; and

Adhere to 
Sections 116(d) and 2.2 of COA Circular Nos. 2003-003 and 2006-002 dated 
June 20, 2002 and January 31, 2006, respectively, requiring the issuance of Obligation Request to accompany the Purchase Request for the appropriations to meet contract or as a pre-requisite of the procurement.

